{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3376568,"name":"Emil","username":"GronkBaby","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/ba8739/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-04-29T16:02:15.163Z","cooked":"<p>I want to run faster periodics and more complicated matrix computations on a coprocessor, rather than the Roborio. How do I go about implementing a periodic, similar to how WPILIb Command Based code works (does the WPIlib provided image for a Raspberry Pi already incorporate this? Does it apply for an OrangePi?) Does anyone have any tips or advice for using coprocessors?</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":12,"updated_at":"2024-04-29T16:02:15.163Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":135,"reads":414,"readers_count":413,"score":752.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":464861,"topic_slug":"working-with-coprocessors-specifically-orange-pi","display_username":"Emil","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":64351,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/working-with-coprocessors-specifically-orange-pi/464861/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3376576,"name":"Jade","username":"spacey_sooty","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/spacey_sooty/{size}/256378_2.png","created_at":"2024-04-29T16:16:02.045Z","cooked":"<p>You can actually run a WPILib project on a coprocessor to do certain stuff. The best tips I can give are<br>
A. Utilise network tables heavily for communication with the roboRIO its the best way to communicate with the roboRIO.<br>
B. Get a decently workable deployment pipeline. If you go down the WPILib project on a coprocessor then you can utilise GradleRIO for deployment which can be nice.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":12,"updated_at":"2024-04-29T16:16:02.045Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":406,"readers_count":405,"score":91.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":464861,"topic_slug":"working-with-coprocessors-specifically-orange-pi","display_username":"Jade","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":60214,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"4788 | Choreo | PhotonVision"},"post_url":"/t/working-with-coprocessors-specifically-orange-pi/464861/2","custom_user_title":"4788 | Choreo | PhotonVision","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3376635,"name":"Emil","username":"GronkBaby","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/g/ba8739/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-04-29T17:10:52.783Z","cooked":"<p>Awesome! Do you know if OrangePi or other coprocessors allow for multithreading?</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":12,"updated_at":"2024-04-29T17:10:52.783Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":365,"readers_count":364,"score":78.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":464861,"topic_slug":"working-with-coprocessors-specifically-orange-pi","display_username":"Emil","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":60214,"username":"spacey_sooty","name":"Jade","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/spacey_sooty/{size}/256378_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":64351,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/working-with-coprocessors-specifically-orange-pi/464861/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3376682,"name":"Max","username":"Napkino","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/eb9ed0/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-04-29T17:45:17.074Z","cooked":"<p>The OPi 5 has multiple cores on its processor, so you should be able to run multiple threads at once, from what I understand at least. I don’t <em>think</em> there’s any special requirements or anything on an Orange Pi, but I’ve never done anything custom with them, so I don’t have any experience there.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":12,"updated_at":"2024-04-29T17:46:47.252Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":348,"readers_count":347,"score":74.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":464861,"topic_slug":"working-with-coprocessors-specifically-orange-pi","display_username":"Max","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,