ted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/working-with-coprocessors-specifically-orange-pi/464861/5","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3377139,"name":"joemost","username":"joemost","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/joemost/{size}/11114_2.png","created_at":"2024-04-30T11:30:58.281Z","cooked":"<p>I’d assume as long as you can get the relevant version of Java to work on the coprocessor, it’ll work fine.</p>
<p>6328 did some offboard computations on Orange Pis on their 2023 Robot. I didn’t look at the code but I bet they streamed it back to their Rio via NetworkTables and then handled all the logging from there.</p>
<p>You might want to go that route instead.</p>
