alculations that take slipping wheels and collisions into account. To get a high frequency on every cycle, I’d rather do it on a coprocessor.</p>
<p>It’s probably not necessary to use one - but it’s a good learning opportunity for me.</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":12,"updated_at":"2024-04-30T13:41:42.811Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":209,"readers_count":208,"score":41.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":464861,"topic_slug":"working-with-coprocessors-specifically-orange-pi","display_username":"Emil","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":20003,"username":"joemost","name":"joemost","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/joemost/{size}/11114_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":64351,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/working-with-coprocessors-specifically-orange-pi/464861/7","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3377663,"name":"Joe Ross","username":"Joe_Ross","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/joe_ross/{size}/37_2.png","created_at":"2024-05-01T01:51:04.959Z","cooked":"<p>Besides update rate, it’s also important to consider the latency that your processing architecture imparts. Lets say you’re taking vision measurements from a limelight and sending to the Orange Pi, and taking sensor measurements from the roboRIO and sending to the Orange Pi, and then sending the result back to the roboRIO which then has to send a command to a motor controller, you may find that you actually get better results running a simpler algorithm on the roboRIO, at a lower rate with less latency.</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":12,"updated_at":"2024-05-01T01:51:04.959Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":159,"readers_count":158,"score":61.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":464861,"topic_slug":"working-with-coprocessors-specifically-orange-pi","display_username":"Joe Ross","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":true,"admin":false,"staff":true,"user_id":65,"hidden":false,"trust_level":4,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/working-with-coprocessors-specifically-orange-pi/464861/8","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3380607,"name":"joel truher","username":"truher","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/truher/{size}/172222_2.png","created_at":"2024-05-06T13:23:45.593Z","cooked":"<p>I’m interested in gradle deploys for our coprocessors.  does anyone know of a successful example?</p>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":12,"updated_at":"2024-05-06T13:23:45.593Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":117,"readers_count":116,"score":33.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":464861,"topic_slug":"working-with-coprocessors-specifically-orange-pi","display_username":"joel truher","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":60214,"username":"spacey_sooty","name":"Jade","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/spacey_sooty/{size}/256378_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":53190,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/working-with-coprocessors-specifically-orange-pi/464861/9","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3380674,"name":"Jade","username":"spacey_sooty","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/spacey_sooty/{size}/256378_2.png","created_at":"2024-05-06T15:28:41.116Z","cooked":"<p>I have some oldish ones? They would probably take a bit of legwork to get up and running.<br>
